parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power steering and power brakes, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the ignition switch is difficult to turn
the vehicle takes multiple attempts to start
the dash lights flash or flicker
the vehicle hesitates or surges when starting
the engine dies while idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power steering and power brakes, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the dash lights flash or flicker
the vehicle takes multiple attempts to start
the engine dies while idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air condition unit can cause smoke to enter the vehicle, which can be a distraction to the driver and increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The air condition unit stops working
smoke enters the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle may not be adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of airbag inflator parts can prevent the timely repair of recalled vehicles, leaving owners at risk of airbag failure in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Dealerships are unable to obtain the necessary parts to repair recalled vehicles
resulting in delayed or incomplete repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate or misleading recall notifications can lead to confusion and frustration among vehicle owners, potentially delaying necessary repairs.
symptoms: Vehicle owners receive incorrect or unclear information about airbag recalls
or are told that their vehicle is not affected by a recall when it actually is.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which may not deploy properly in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard remains illuminated
indicating a potential issue with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates
slips
or shudders when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes a loud noise
the vehicle stalls
the transmission fluid leaks
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly when in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the input shift bearing can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission makes a grinding or loud noise
the transmission hesitates or slips when shifting gears
the transmission fluid leaks.
